HEADWORD: Gothamist
<hw>Go"tham*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wiseacre; a
person deficient in wisdom; -- so called from Gotham, in
Nottinghamshire, England, noted for some pleasant blunders.</def>
<rj><au>Bp. Morton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gothamite</ent>⟦br⟧
